$ Perl operator: || (bar bar)

The *slash slash* operator in perl returns the left side value *if* it is true, otherwise it returns the right side value. This differs from the → development/languages/Perl/operators/slash_slash[// operator] in that the `// operator` checks
for definendness rather than truth.

gh|about-perl|/operators/bar_bar.pl||

sa:
  → development/languages/Perl/operators/[Perl operators]
